(secondQuint)Chloroquine for Symptomatic Persistent and Longstanding Persistent AF.

 This is an open-label, pilot study to explore the efficacy of chloroquine in terminating persistent and longstanding persistent AF within 2 weeks of drug administration and assess its potential role as a pharmacological cardioversion agent for the management of AF.

 Subjects will be followed for 2 weeks from the start of drug administration to study drug termination.

